import re

def normalize_name(name):
    return re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', name).title()
```

```python
def normalize_name(name):
    return name.strip().title().strip().lower()
```

This function uses the `strip()` method to remove extra spaces and the `title()` method to capitalize the first letter of each word. The `title()` method converts the string to title case, which is a case-insensitive way to convert a string to title case.

